## 🚀 AMFF-Net: Innovative Experiments & Usage

This section provides official instructions to reproduce the core innovations proposed in our manuscript: the **Adaptive Multi-Frequency Fusion Network (AMFF-Net)** and the **Frequency Attention Module (FAM)** for cross-generator synthetic image detection.

### 1. Environment & Data Preparation

Ensure that your environment is configured and the datasets are properly linked. 

```bash
# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Ensure the datasets folder is properly symlinked to your data directory
ln -s /path/to/your/datasets ./datasets
2. Training the AMFF-Net (Multi-Band Fusion)
To train the proposed AMFF-Net with the Frequency Attention Module, we utilize the multi-band fine-tuning script. This pipeline extracts ultra-high (HH), high (HL/LH), and low (LL) frequency components and dynamically aligns them.

You can start the training process using the provided shell script:

Bash
bash scripts/train_mb.sh
Alternatively, to run the training manually with custom hyperparameters:

Bash
python main_finetune_mb.py \
    --model safe_mb_attention \
    --batch_size 64 \
    --epochs 50 \
    --lr 1e-4 \
    --data_path ./datasets/train_data \
    --output_dir ./results/diffusion_trained_model
Note: The --model safe_mb_attention flag explicitly activates our proposed FAM module.

3. Cross-Domain Evaluation
To evaluate the zero-shot generalization ability of the trained AMFF-Net on unseen diffusion models or legacy GAN architectures:

Bash
bash scripts/eval_mb.sh
For detailed robustness evaluation against real-world degradations (e.g., JPEG compression, blurring), run the specific robustness script:

Bash
bash scripts/eval_robustness.sh
The evaluation results, including Accuracy and Average Precision (AP), will be automatically saved to ./results/eval_results_ours.csv.

4. Ablation Studies
To verify the effectiveness of individual frequency bands and the necessity of the proposed attention mechanism versus naive concatenation, execute the ablation suite:

Bash
bash scripts/run_ablation.sh
Logs for the ablation studies will be documented in ./results/ablation/ablation.log.

5. Visualization & Analysis Tools
A key contribution of our work is mitigating "frequency bias". We provide several tools to visualize the internal mechanics of AMFF-Net and provide interpretable insights.

Extract Frequency Heatmaps:
Visualizes the spectral energy distribution differences between Real, GAN, and Diffusion images.

Bash
python tools/frequency_heatmaps.py --input_dir ./test_data_level_1/ --output_dir ./assets/
Visualize Frequency Attention Weights (FAM):
Generates attention maps to demonstrate how AMFF-Net dynamically re-weights frequency bands to avoid signal dampening.

Bash
python tools/vis_attention.py --checkpoint ./results/diffusion_trained_model/checkpoint-best.pth
t-SNE Feature Space Visualization:
Compares the feature clustering between the baseline model and AMFF-Net.

Bash
python tools/vis_tsne_comparison.py
